\v 3 Ez…® Jeremaia aning…®n akam ikaragha ghaze, ‚ÄúGua mang…® Sedekaia m…®k…®m suam,  
\v 4 Ikiav…®ra Itir God, a Israelian God, kamagh…®n m…®g…®a ghaze, ‚ÄòDat…®r…®gh…®n Babilon…®n atrivim, Kaldiabar m…®dorozir gumaziba ko iza Jerusalem…®n d…®vazim ek…®aru. Ez…® Israelian m…®dorozir gumaziba m…®dorozir bizibar suigha d…®vazim…®n azenan gara Babilonia ko m…®sosi. Eght…® k…® ian m…®dorozir bizir kabagh iraght…®, da nguibar ekiam…®n tong…®ra ik…®t…®, k…® kagh bar mogh…®ra da akuvagh pozir ekiam m…®k…®nigham.  
\v 5 K…® uab…® bar ian an…®ngaghegh ian atar…®va uan gavgavim sara ia m…®sogh bar ia gas…®ghasigham.  
\v 6 Egh k…® nguibar ekiar kam…®n aven itir gumazamiziba ko as…®zitaba ar…®mariar kuraba me danight…®, me ar…®m…®ghiregham.  
\v 7 K…® Ikiav…®ra Itir God k…® ua kamagh…®n m…®gei. Gumazamizir av…®rim, ar…®mariar kaba ko, m…®dorozir kam ko, dagheba puvat…®ghamin dughiam bang…®n ar…®ghiram. Egh g…®n k…® Atrivim Nebukatnesar ko an m…®dorozir gumaziba ateght…®, me Atrivim Sedekaia uan gumazir ekiaba ko gumazamizir ikiav…®ra itiba inigh mangam. Apanir kaba Israelia ia m…®soght…® ia aremeghasa bar ifonge. Nebukatnesar kuarkuvim ko, ifongiam ko, apangkuvir arazim tong ian ikeghan kogham. Egh ian tav ateght…®, a ikian kogham.‚Äô‚Äâ‚Äù 
